description.narrative: Enhanced capacity of 455 statutory workers (67 social workers, 388 health workers) on child protection (CP) helped improve delivery of social welfare, birth registration (BR) and case management services to children. The strengthened capacity of health workers contributed to the registration and certification of at least 112,249 children under 13, of which 41,626 children (20,131 boys, 21,495 girls), or 22.7%, were children under age 5; and 32,800 children (17,167 boys, 15,633 girls), or 35.2%, were children under age 1. Another 1,426 children (708 boys, 718 girls) who experienced violence were reached by health, social work or justice services. | Status:Met | As-of Date:31/12/2019
